"Jin: Hey Megan, just got back! It was a really interesting experience participating in a youth leadership forum at Hac-Sa Nautical Centre.\nMegan: Oh, that sounds\u2026 involved! How was the travel getting there and back?\nJin: It was pretty smooth, thankfully. Honestly, the whole thing was a bit of a whirlwind, a lot of new faces and ideas. It was a great opportunity for professional development.\nMegan: That\u2019s fantastic, Jin! It\u2019s always good to invest in yourself, and sounds like it was worth it. I've been swamped with kiwi chicks needing check-ups, it's been nonstop.\nJin: That sounds hectic! I bet they\u2019re adorable though. Back home, the restaurant is always busy, so I'm looking forward to getting back into the kitchen.\nMegan: You always make it sound so peaceful! Running a restaurant must be incredibly fulfilling. What's the newest thing on the menu?\nJin: Actually, I was hoping to try a new kimchi recipe inspired by some of the discussions we had there, stemming from the trip\u2019s youth leadership forum. It's a long shot, but you never know!\nMegan: Ooh, a kimchi innovation! That's exciting - you always come up with the most creative combinations. \nJin: Thanks! It\u2019s all about experimenting and pushing boundaries. How long are you in hospital taking care of the chicks?\nMegan: At least another month, they need round-the-clock care for the first few weeks. Then it's onto the next batch! It's a good problem to have, really."
