"Thomas: Just got back from Fore School of Management. It was quite an experience being there for a temporary non-profit assignment.\nDaria: Oh, that sounds\u2026involved! How was the travel getting there and back?\nThomas: A bit hectic, honestly. But rewarding. I was helping to restore some of the older woodwork in a community building just behind it. The craftsmanship wasn\u2019t quite to my standards, naturally.\nDaria: You're such a perfectionist! It's admirable, though. I always tell my skaters, the details are everything.\nThomas: Exactly! A slightly misaligned joint can weaken the whole structure, you see. It's much the same with a wobbly landing on the ice, I imagine.\nDaria: Absolutely. Everything builds on everything else. One tiny flaw can throw off the entire routine. What kind of wood were you working with?\nThomas: Mostly teak and rosewood, unfortunately a lot of it had suffered water damage. Required some pretty delicate work to bring it back.\nDaria: That sounds incredibly painstaking. My hands just ache thinking about the precision needed.\nThomas: It is. But seeing a piece of history revitalised\u2026 that\u2019s the real reward. It\u2019s more fulfilling than any modern construction, I assure you. \nDaria: I can believe that! There\u2019s something special about preserving the past, isn\u2019t there? It connects us to those who came before."
