"Evan: Hey Sophia, just wanted to let you know I was recently at Yahya Yuhana Mandi attending a business conference. It was a bit different from what I'm used to, but productive!\nSophia: Oh, that sounds\u2026busy. How was the travel getting there? I've been mostly tied up with cataloging finds from the last dig.\nEvan: It was alright, I actually ended up doing a little improvising at the dance studio just behind Yahya Yuhana Mandi \u2013 a great way to unwind after long conference days. The trip was primarily for attending a business conference, so it wasn't all work, thankfully.\nSophia: That's fantastic, Evan! Finding a creative outlet while traveling is so important. It keeps the mind fresh.\nEvan: It really does. I was a little worried about being away from my piano for so long, but a keyboard was available. It wasn't the same, but it helped a lot.\nSophia: I can only imagine. Instruments are such a direct extension of oneself. Are you working on any new compositions at the moment?\nEvan: Actually, yes. I\u2019m trying to incorporate some of the rhythmic patterns I heard while traveling into a new piece, something a bit more\u2026global, I guess.\nSophia: That\u2019s fascinating. Blending different influences can lead to really exciting results. I find the same thing happens with archaeological work and interpreting different cultures.\nEvan: Exactly! It\u2019s all about finding connections and building something new. Speaking of new, how\u2019s the research going? Anything particularly exciting unearthed recently?\nSophia: We\u2019ve uncovered a remarkably well-preserved mosaic depicting a scene from the Odyssey. It's quite fragile, so it\u2019s consuming a lot of time with conservation efforts, but it's worth it.\n\n\n\n"
