"Carmen: Hi Lucas! Just wanted to share that I was at the Roman amphitheatre of Leptis Magna recently taking a professional arts masterclass. It was incredible!\nLucas: Oh, that sounds...intense! Been keeping pretty busy myself, just trying to keep the tomatoes from splitting with all this rain.\nCarmen: It was truly inspiring. The masterclass focused on ancient storytelling techniques. We even did some improvisational exercises in the dance studio just behind the Roman amphitheatre of Leptis Magna! \nLucas: Improvisation, huh? I tried a little acting once, in a community theatre production. Let's just say my natural talent lies elsewhere.\nCarmen: Oh, that's fantastic you gave it a go! This masterclass was specifically geared toward enriching arts education programs, which connects to my work at the library.\nLucas: That\u2019s a really admirable goal, Carmen. Libraries are essential. I always appreciate a good researched book when trying out a new growing technique.\nCarmen: Exactly! I'm hoping to implement some of the storytelling methods in my children's story hours. It's all about engaging them on a deeper level.\nLucas: That sounds wonderful. Getting kids excited about stories is a really important thing. I try to do the same with vegetables!\nCarmen: Haha, I can imagine! Anything that sparks curiosity. It was a pretty unique experience going on this trip for taking a professional arts masterclass.\nLucas: Well, I'm glad you had a good time. I'm off to build another raised bed before the weather turns again. Talk to you soon!"
