"Carmen: Hello Bruno! It was wonderful being at Marapendi Club, I was going on a birdwatching expedition.\nBruno: Carmen, that sounds\u2026 different for you! What sparked your interest in birdwatching?\nCarmen: Well, I've always loved nature documentaries, and I thought it would be a peaceful way to spend some time outdoors, away from the library.\nBruno: Peaceful sounds good. I\u2019ve been trying to find time to just *be* lately. My students are very energetic, as you can imagine.\nCarmen: Oh, I can imagine! Working with children takes a lot of energy. I'm actually planning a special story hour next month focusing on environmental awareness.\nBruno: That's a great idea! Instilling respect for nature in young people is crucial. Have you found any good books on the subject?\nCarmen: I have! Several actually. I\u2019m trying to find one featuring diverse bird species that's accessible for younger readers.\nBruno: That\u2019s important. Representation matters, even in nature books. It\u2019s the same with capoeira \u2013 showing its roots and history is vital.\nCarmen: Absolutely! Speaking of roots, how is your new student progressing with the more advanced movements?\nBruno: Slowly but surely! He's got the rhythm, just needs to build up strength. It's a process, like everything worthwhile."
