"Carmen: Oh, hello Omar! You won\u2019t believe where I just was \u2013 Jong's Crocodile Farm and Zoo. It was quite an experience!\nOmar: Carmen! Good to see you. How have you been keeping? Anything new happening with the library?\nCarmen: Things are busy as always! I was actually there for attending a collectors' show, believe it or not, right next to the farm. It was fascinating to see so many unique items.\nOmar: A collectors' show, that sounds interesting. I\u2019ve been mostly focused on a large commission for a new bookshelf, it's taking up all my time.\nCarmen: A bookshelf sounds lovely! I'm always looking for ways to improve the library's displays. Perhaps you could create something for us?\nOmar: I might consider it, though my schedule is pretty full at the moment. I\u2019m trying to save up for new tools, you see.\nCarmen: That's understandable! Good tools are essential. We just hosted a wonderful author talk last week, a local poet.\nOmar: Oh, that's nice. I haven't much time for poetry these days, but I do enjoy listening to music while I work. Classical Arabic, mostly.\nCarmen: Music is so important. It really sets the mood. We have a small but growing collection of world music at the library.\nOmar: That sounds like a wonderful resource for the community. Anyway, it was good chatting with you, Carmen! I need to get back to the workshop. \n\n\n\n"
