"Jayden: Hey Adriana, just wanted to let you know I was at Christian Reformed Church Jalingo, conducting thesis research. It was a really intense experience.\nAdriana: Oh, that sounds\u2026 involved! Thesis work is never easy, is it? What are you researching, if you don\u2019t mind my asking?\nJayden: It's actually related to spatial acoustics \u2013 how sound behaves in different architectural spaces. The church building provided a very unique environment for data collection. It was actually quite a challenge finding the right recording equipment!\nAdriana: Acoustic studies, fascinating! I deal with a lot of underwater recordings myself, and the equipment can be a nightmare. Noise pollution is a huge problem, even for marine life.\nJayden: Totally! Even a slight hum can ruin hours of recording. Speaking of challenges, getting everything set up for thesis research took forever. There were so many variables!\nAdriana: I can imagine. You have to account for practically everything, it sounds like. I'm currently trying to model coral bleaching events, the amount of data is overwhelming.\nJayden: That sounds incredibly important. It's good you're working on something so vital. Do you ever get discouraged when analyzing all the negative trends?\nAdriana: Some days, definitely. But then I remember why I started and the potential for positive change, that helps a lot. What motivates you when things get tough with your research?\nJayden: For me, it\u2019s the thought of applying what I learn to improve the game experience, especially for competitive play. That's where my passion really lies. \nAdriana: That\u2019s great! It\u2019s so important to have a clear vision for your work. It makes all the difference when facing those inevitable hurdles.\n\n\n\n"
